sql:
SELECT reading_time
FROM sensor_readings
ORDER BY reading_time;

SELECT distance_value 
FROM prev_distances 
WHERE side_id = 0 AND timestamp < '2023-05-01 12:00:00';

SELECT side_id, distance_value
FROM new_distances
WHERE expected_time_to_collision < 10.0;

SELECT side_name, description
FROM sides
WHERE relative_position = 'center';

SELECT AVG(metric_value) AS average_std_dev, COUNT(*) AS count_of_std_dev
FROM data_quality_metrics
WHERE metric_name = 'std_dev';

SELECT DISTINCT reading_value
FROM sensor_readings
WHERE ignore = 0;

external_knowledge:
High-quality data refers to data where the mean value in the data_quality_metrics table is above 0.8; 
Average confidence level refers to the average confidence level in the sensor readings for each sensor type;
At least one alert means the count of alert_id is greater than 0.
